Conclusion: both deployed eps values (1e-5, 1e-6) are below the
FP16 subnormal threshold (2^-14 = 6.1e-5), so a subnormal rsqrt
input requires variance+eps itself to round below 2^-14, i.e. a
near-zero hidden-state variance. The profiling above shows how
rarely this occurs and where (per layer, per model).
